      "amount": "1/2 cup (50 g)",
      "notes": "nut\u2011free coconut only"
    },
    {
      "name": "appleton rum",
      "amount": "1 tbsp (15 ml)",
      "notes": "adds smoky aroma"
    },
    {
      "name": "vegetable oil",
      "amount": "1 tbsp (14 g)",
      "notes": "for frying"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "In a large bowl whisk together flour, baking powder, coriander, cumin, turmeric, smoked paprika, and salt.",
    "Stir in sugar, coconut milk, appleton rum, and a splash of oil until a thick batter forms.",
    "Fold in grated coconut until evenly distributed.",
    "Heat 1-2 inches of vegetable oil in a deep skillet to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C).",
    "Drop spoonfuls of batter into the hot oil, leaving space between each fritter.",
    "Fry for 2-3 minutes on each side until golden and crisp.",
    "Use a slotted spoon to transfer fritters to paper towels to drain excess oil.",
    "Serve warm, optionally dusted with a pinch of sea salt."
  ],
